The paper proposes a new sequential recommendation model that uses self-attention mechanism to capture long-term semantics and make predictions based on relatively few actions. This work involves machine learning and natural language processing techniques, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
